&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;You are a data-driven, hands-on leader who operates with a relentless focus on foundational software quality, developer experience (DX), data integrity, and strict operational metrics. In this role, you’ll eliminate traditional silos by directly managing both product and engineering tracks into a singular, high-velocity infrastructure and platform machine. You deeply care about making both our internal engineering teams and developer partners successful, championing platform design, modern frameworks, and robust developer tools to ensure Hyperproof scales smoothly. You understand how crucial it is to architect data pipelines that integrate into modern systems for crucial workflows from AI ingestion to dashboarding to analytics.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;You stretch beyond AI and extensibility into hands on software infrastructure, leading and operating a world class developer operations team that deliver mission critical developer tooling and build automation to the rest of the organization and our partners.&amp;nbsp; You architect these systems for speed of execution, quality and compliance with our FedRAMP Moderate obligations.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;You will partner closely with Applications, Security, Data, Architecture, Operations, and Risk Governance teams to ensure Hyperproof&#39;s infrastructure is secure, governed, observable, reliable, and cost-effective as we scale to meet the demands of the modern enterprise market.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
